Architecture Overview

Based on a Client-Server model

Utilizes the MVC architecture for better maintainability

Frontend communicates with backend via API layer

Core Modules

Frontend: Dynamic UI, input validation, chatbot interface

Backend: Handles routes, processes input, and triggers AI

AI Engine: Performs NLP tasks like intent recognition

Data Module: Stores queries, responses, and user history

Utilities: Helper functions for preprocessing and model loading

